snippet.textDisplay: Oh tana 💔 i went through these feeling last year, having to be the adult growing up with parents who didn’t know how to be parents is hard and the transition into adulthood in your early twenties really bring all of those feelings of reflection and regret that your childhood was and never will be normal is fucking HARD. Especially when you begin to see people (who’s family life is by no means perfect but) at dream come true in your eyes when you compare it to your own experience. I felt all of those feeling as you watched Jorden’s family interact the way they did, when i spent the holidays or even just normal days of the year with my ex and it really made me do all sorts of mental acrobats about why it seems so natural and easy for them when it wasn’t for me or my family. Now I’m in a better place of expectance thankfully, i cherish the time i have with my blood relatives although they often aren’t always amazing and sometimes even heart wrenching and difficult, but i thrive off of my chosen family: my friends who love me, my family members who have step up to the plate an admitted their wrong, and myself for always taking care of me the best i knew how to. I know you can get through this and find that, you are still so young and have time to make your own traditions and change your life to be the one you wish you had been given as a child! I hope you find the clarity and acceptance, and know you are seen and not alone💕

snippet.textDisplay:
honestly i had super shitty parents too, fairly similar to tana's and with a lot of alcohol, and at some point you sadly have to learn to accept it.. you realize that they had their own problems too and just because they weren't good parents doesn't mean they're terrible people always. you kinda have to learn how to turn that relationship into a friendship when you have a hard time looking at them as "parents". nothing will change the past but they won't be around forever so if you do still want a relationship with them try and make it less of a parent/child relationship if that makes any sense lol.
(also i realize sometimes parents do things that are completely unforgivable and you're allowed to cut toxic people out of your life if you please, even your parents. but this is more for those who want to move forward i guess)
